<p style="font-size: 18px; margin: 0px 0px 12px;">This topic describes the deployment architecture, system requirements, pre-requisites, and steps to install and configure Network Automation (NA).</p><p style="font-size: 18px; margin: 0px 0px 12px;">A full installation of Network Automation includes the following components:</p><ul style="margin-left: 18px; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 18px;"><li><p style="margin: 0px 0px 18px;"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Core components</span></p><ul style="margin-left: 18px; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 4px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><li style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-bottom: 0.65em;">NA Core - The central unit responsible for performing key monitoring and automation tasks.</li></ul><ul style="margin-left: 18px; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 4px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><li style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-bottom: 0.65em;">Database- Acts as a repository of configuration data collected from devices connected to NA.</li></ul></li><li><p style="margin: 0px 0px 18px;"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Other components (Optional)</span></p><ul style="margin-left: 18px; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 4px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><li style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-bottom: 0.65em;">Core gateway, Remote gateway, Remote Agent - These components manage data over a firewall in a secure environment. Together they form a Satellite.</li></ul></li></ul><p style="font-size: 18px; margin: 0px 0px 12px;">Depending on the organizational requirements, create one of the following environments:</p><ul style="margin-left: 18px; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 18px;"><li>A single NA Core with an internal or external database.</li><li>Multiple NA Cores with a single, centralized database to create a scalable environment to distribute the load of managing large networks.</li><li>Multiple NA Cores with multiple databases to create a multimaster setup.</li></ul><p style="font-size: 18px; margin: 0px 0px 12px;">For network devices that are present in a secure environment, you can install NA Satellite to enable communication and monitoring over the firewall.</p><p style="font-size: 18px; margin: 0px 0px 12px;">To complete the installation of Network Automation:</p><ol style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 4px; margin-top: 0px; margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 0.65em; font-size: 18px;"><li style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-bottom: 0.65em; margin-top: 0.65em;">Choose the deployment architecture.</li><li style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-bottom: 0.65em; margin-top: 0.65em;">Review the system requirements.</li><li style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-bottom: 0.65em; margin-top: 0.65em;">Perform the pre-installation tasks, run the setup file, and perform the post installation tasks.</li><li style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-bottom: 0.65em; margin-top: 0.65em;">(Optional)Install the Core gateway, remote gateway and remote agent.</li></ol>